<article class="about-page">
  <h1>About This Directory</h1>

  <p>The Florida Court Mediation Directory is an independent informational resource designed to help attorneys, self-represented litigants, mediators, and court staff find contact information and program details for court mediation across all 20 judicial circuits in Florida.</p>

  <h2>What You'll Find Here</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Circuit Pages</strong> — Contact information, programs offered, county-specific contacts, and notes for each of Florida's 20 judicial circuits.</li>
    <li><strong>County Lookup</strong> — A quick search tool to find which circuit serves your county.</li>
    <li><strong>Program Overview</strong> — An explanation of the different types of court mediation available in Florida, including fees, eligibility, and statewide trends.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Data Sources</h2>
  <p>All information is compiled from publicly available sources, including official circuit court websites, the Florida Courts website, and the Florida Dispute Resolution Center. We make every effort to keep this information current and accurate.</p>

  <h2>Disclaimer</h2>
  <p>{{ settings.disclaimer }}</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>If you notice outdated information or have suggestions for improvement, please reach out via the official channels for the relevant circuit court. For general questions about mediation in Florida, visit the <a href="https://www.flcourts.gov/Resources-Services/Alternative-Dispute-Resolution" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Florida Dispute Resolution Center</a>.</p>
</article>
